When drawing connected terrain, use PageUp/PageDown to adjust the terrain placement height.
Hold Alt to place celltags in a straight line.
You can quickly save the map with the F1 shortcut keyРђћno dialog box will pop up.
In the Trigger Editor, you can drag behaviors from the list to multiple open editor windows.
You can customize the colors of waypoints and celltags for easier identification.
Hold Ctrl and drag a unit to quickly change its facing, supporting 32 directions.
Default properties for buildings, infantry, etc., can be set in FAData.ini.
The map can be rendered as an image, and batch processing of multiple maps is supported.
Through Lua scripts, you can read and modify map data to automate operations.
You can use the Lua script terminal to execute script brushes for batch operations.
In map notes, you can add comments for triggers, teams, etc.
Supports reading ini files exported by Ra2CsfToolsGUI as CSF text.
In multi-select mode, you can hide selected cells for better observation.
Map files can be associated with the launcherРђћjust double-click to open.
You can set a custom light source direction for VXL units to adjust rendering effects.
Supports displaying cloaked units as semiРђЉtransparent.
You can use the distance ruler to measure the distance between two points on the map.
Supports batch filling of terrain in multiРђЉselected areas with a specified type.
You can preview thumbnails of all units and terrains in the Object Browser.
Use Global Search to quickly locate units, waypoints, or coordinates.
Supports ignoring specific overlays or objects per theater type.
Terrain group presets can be saved as presets_XXX.map files for reuse.
Supports retaining comments and INI section order when saving maps.
You can set custom large and small water indices for each theater.
You can set the owner color for fence overlays based on the nearest building.
Supports precise placement of infantry in subРђЉcells of terrain.
Use the Terrain Generator to randomly generate terrain based on Perlin noise.
Supports rendering shadows for VXL unit turrets and barrels.
Use the shortcut Ctrl+Shift+O to quickly reload the current map.
Supports PhobosРђЉstyle player house tags (e.g., <Player @ AРђЉH>) for multiplayer maps.
You can add map notes and doubleРђЉclick them to quickly edit the content.
Use the brush to batch change the owner of units on the map.
Customize the types and rules of connected terrain via ConnectedTileDrawer.ini.
Configure automatic conversion rules when pasting across different terrains via TileConvertRules.ini.
Use FADialog.ini to translate any FA2 dialog text for a fully localized interface.
Place custom images like target.bmp or celltag.bmp into the [pics] folder to replace default icons.
On a crash, the map is automatically backed up to the CrashBackups folder with a timestamp.
Object Browser thumbnails are cached in the thumbnails folder, loading faster after the first generation.
Put highРђЉpriority resources into the Resources\HighPriority folder to load them first.
Configure nested MIX file loading order via [NestedMixes] for flexible resource management.
Set up encrypted resource packages in [ExtraPackages] to protect your original assets.
Load additional CSF, LLF, or ECS string tables using [ExtraStringtables].
Define new LAT terrain groups via [LATGroups] and [LATSettings] to support mod expansions.
Customize the brush size list in [BrushSizes].
Configure multiple shore styles per theater via [AutoShoreTypes] and switch them in real time.
Use [SoftTileSetsXXX] to control whether autoРђЉshore affects specific terrain sets.
Specify terrain sets that need a second draw of ExtraImage via [RedrawExtraTileSetsXXX].
Prevent specific terrains from blocking elevated bridge overlays using [NoExtraHeightRedrawTileSetsXXX].
Categorize overlays in the Object Browser with [ObjectBrowser.Overlays] for easier browsing.
Hide unwanted overlays in the Object Browser via [IgnoreOverlays].
ForceРђЉtranslate object IDs with [RenameID] regardless of the original language files.
Ignore certain units or overlays in the Map Renderer via [MapRendererIgnoreObjects].
Register random placement presets in sections like [PlaceRandomTileList].
When a map file is located in a different game folder, FA2 prompts whether to reload the corresponding resources.
Type text in dropРђЉdown menus to quickly search, supporting * and | wildcards.
Use the РђюFind ReferencesРђЮ feature to quickly locate which triggers or teams reference the current object.
OneРђЉclick РђюAutoРђЉcompute LATРђЮ fixes terrain connections across the whole map to match inРђЉgame logic.
Use the РђюRedraw WaterРђЮ feature to repair incomplete water bodies, making them more natural.
Turn on the РђюImpassable CellsРђЮ layer to visually see which cells units cannot reach.
Filter layers to show only specific types of objects, reducing visual clutter.
In the Terrain Generator, you can directly use multiРђЉselected areas as the generation range without manual setup.
Override game settings with ini files prefixed with fa2extra_.
Use [ForceSides] to place the same techno type into multiple groups in the Object Browser.
When placing walls, you can choose different damage levels, and the system will automatically connect adjacent walls.
Press Delete to quickly delete selected objects.
A thin blue line at the top of the map indicates the actual reachable upper boundary in the game.
The paste options let you paste only specific types, such as terrain or overlays.
When importing a map from a BMP, you can specify the target theater type (e.g., Temperate).
When placing buildings, automatic overlap checking can be enabled, with an option to force placement.
Hold Shift for steep raising, creating twoРђЉcellРђЉhigh cliffs.
Hold Shift+Ctrl to force raising even on terrain that normally cannot be raised.
Consecutive terrain or overlay placements are merged into a single undo step.
In multiplayer maps, waypoints start from 8 to avoid conflict with player start locations.
Use the РђюRemove Ore on RampsРђЮ Lua script to quickly clear ore placed on slopes.
Use the РђюRandom Ore ImagesРђЮ Lua script to make ore appearances more varied.
When the number of elements in the drop-down menu or list exceeds SearchCombobox.MaxCount (default is 1000), you need to press Enter to do the search.